evidence.title: Please
evidence.text: you please, an intransitive, ergative form taken from if it please you, which is in turn a calque of the French s'il vous plaît, which replaced pray. The exact time frame of the shortening is unknown, though it has been noted that this form appears not to have been known to William Shakespeare, for whom "please you" is the shortest form used in any of his works. evidence.title: Suits LA
evidence.text: Suits LA is an American legal drama television series created by Aaron Korsh for NBC. It is the second spin-off of Suits and premiered on February 23, 2025. In May 2025, the series was cancelled after one season. Premise Ex-New York City federal prosecutor turned Los Angeles entertainment lawyer Ted Black and his Black Lane Law firm represent powerful clients in LA while Ted and his associates navigate personal and professional challenges.
